{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:32:39.308571+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here's a summary of how to install, configure, and deploy the React Firebase starter template:\n\n## 📦 Installation\n\nYou can install this template using either `npx` or `yarn`:\n\n**Using npx:**\n```bash\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\n**Using yarn:**\n```bash\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\n> Note: There's also a TypeScript version available at [cra-template-typescript-firebase](https://github.com/pettiboy/cra-template-typescript-firebase).\n\n## ⚙️ Firebase Configuration\n\n### 1. Create a Firebase Project\n\n1. Go to the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)\n2. Click **\"Add project\"** and follow the steps to create a project\n3. Click the web icon (</>) to register a web app\n4. Copy the Firebase SDK configuration details\n\n### 2. Set Up Environment Variables\n\nThe template uses environment variables for Firebase configuration. Update the `.env` file in the root of your project with your Firebase config values:\n\n```\nREACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey=your-api-key\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain=your-project.firebaseapp.com\nREACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId=your-project-id\nREACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket=your-project.appspot.com\nREACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId=your-sender-id\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAppId=your-app-id\n```\n\nThese values are read in `template/src/config/firebase.config.js` using `process.env.REACT_APP_*`.\n\n### 3. Enable Google Authentication\n\n1. In your Firebase console, go to **Authentication → Get Started**\n2. Under **Sign-in method**, click **Google**\n3. Toggle **Enable** and click **Save**\n\n## 🚀 Deploy to GitHub Pages\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n1. **Add your domain to OAuth redirect domains:**\n   - Go to Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method tab\n   - Add your domain (e.g., `your-username.github.io`) to the OAuth redirect domains list\n\n2. **Update `homepage` in `package.json`:**\n   - Change the `homepage` field to your hosting domain\n   - Default format: `http://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name`\n\n### Deploy Commands\n\n**Option A: Test production build locally (optional)**\n```bash\n# Temporarily set homepage to \"/\" in package.json, then:\nnpm i -g serve    # install serve globally\nnpm run build-and-serve\n```\n\n**Option B: Deploy directly to GitHub Pages**\n```bash\nnpm run deploy\n```\n\nThe `deploy` script runs `gh-pages -d build`, which:\n- First runs `npm run build` (via the `predeploy` script)\n- Then publishes the `build/` directory to the `gh-pages` branch\n\n## 🎯 Adding New Screens\n\n1. Create a new component in `src/screens`\n2. Add a route entry in `src/config/routes.js`:\n\n```js\n{\n    path: \"/your-route\",\n    component: YourScreenComponentName,\n    name: \"Screen Name For Reference\",\n    protected: false, // set to true if auth is required\n}\n```\n\n## 🔑 Key Features\n\n- **Routing** with `react-router-dom` (with private route support)\n- **Google Authentication** via Firebase + `react-firebase-hooks`\n- **Material UI** for the login screen UI\n- **GitHub Pages deployment** powered by `gh-pages` and `spa-github-pages`", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 832, "prompt_tokens": 9319, "total_tokens": 10151, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 67, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9088, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002907464, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 5.77864e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00023296}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "syst